The Peace of Nature

I loved the stillness of the night,
  When silence fell from light,
I hear the distant spirits sigh,
  As stars shine in their flight.

In nature's quiet, I behold,
  The truth of life unfold,
Where all is bliss on every plain,
  And the shadows softly hold.

---

- John Greenleaf Whittier
